Overloads for - largestPartialIntersectionWeighted

Module
std.algorithm.setops

largestPartialIntersectionWeighted(ror, tgt, weights, sorted) 

void largestPartialIntersectionWeighted(
  RangeOfRanges ror,
  Range tgt,
  WeightsAA weights,
  SortOutput sorted
)

Similar to largestPartialIntersection , but associates a weight with each distinct element in the intersection.

If at least one of the ranges is a multiset, then all occurences of a duplicate element are taken into account. The result is equivalent to merging all input ranges and picking the highest tgt.length , weight-based ranking elements.

less <parameter not found>

ror RangeOfRanges

ror = A range of $(REF_ALTTEXT forward ranges, isForwardRange, std,range,primitives) sorted by less . tgt = The target range to copy common elements to. weights = An associative array mapping elements to weights. sorted = Whether the elements copied should be in sorted order.
